HEADWORD: Quinoa
<hw>Qui*no"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The seeds of a
kind of goosewort (<spn>Chenopodium Quinoa</spn>), used in Chili and
Peru for making porridge or cakes; also, food thus made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

